[http://assyrianlanguages.org/sureth/index.php Syriac dictionary] says Lešana, or even Lišana. If we would to break down ܠܫܢܐ in how it's actually spelled, it's "L-Š-N-Ā", and with the vowels, how it's pronounced: "Li-Ša-Nā".
I Added a new section, "Modern Arameans", provided sources.

changed "Leššana" to "Lešana". This text is called Romanized, and that means that you write in Latin letter how it's written in the original language. In Syriac the word 'language' is written ܠܫܢܐ, it's written with an 'L' (ܠ), 'š' (ܫ), 'n' (ܢ), and a vowel (ܐ). As you can see there isn't a double-spelling in this word.
changed "Leššana" to "Lešana", it is more accurate because there can never be double spelling in Syriac.
